bare chest as he rams trains on the ground. She reaches down
and picks him up and now he has a shirt on.
She looks toward the skillet and now it’s mac-n-cheese in a
small saucepan that she stirs. It’s evening.
She puts her son down on the ground, and scoops the mac-n-
cheese into two bowls. They sit at the baby table, eating.
The mother sips wine from a real wine glass. She and the boy
cheers.
She lies with the boy in her bed.
