Suddenly on the other end of the park the mother spots the
three dogs she knows, the Brown Dog and the other two. They
are in a pack at the end of the park, and seem to be calling
to the mother, nudging her with their noses in the air. She
looks at them, thinks about it, and then shakes her head
sweetly.
The three dogs exit the park and the mother and her son
continue running and chasing the dogs, while the sun sets
over the park.
INT. MINIATURE TRAIN DISPLAY - DAY142 142
The mother and son make their way through an enormous model
train display that is very cool even for adults: hills with
tiny windmills, small towns with little houses and their
lights on, small scenes of country life with trains chugging
along the tracks. The entire thing is lit up with Christmas
lights and is spectacular.
